<TITLE> Police officer shot dead in old Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 20 (bdnews24.com )  A police officer was shot dead at old Dhaka's Dholaikhal road early on Tuesday. Forty two-year old Goutam Roy, a father of two children who came from Shyamganj in Gouripur upazila of Mymensingh, was the sub-inspector of Banglsal Police Station. Goutam was killed when he was returning to his Wari home from work at around 2:30am, Bangsal police chief Abdul Mannan told bdnews24.com. Goutam was returning home in civilian dress in the jeep of an acquaintance, 'Azam'. Mannan said. The police chief said that Azam told the police that as the jeep came to Dholaikhal road, Goutam saw three young men and had asked him to stop the car. Goutam got out of the vehicle and searched their bodies. At one point, one of the young men shot at Goutam, Hearing gunfire, a patrol police team came to the spot and found Goutam wounded. He was rushed to Dhaka Medical College Hospital (DMCH) where the duty doctor declared him dead. Dhaka Metropolitan Police commissioner AKM Shahidul Haque visited DMCH to see Goutam's body. b
